1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:06,610
Whether you want to believe it or not, Fibonacci
levels play a critical role in defining support

2
00:00:06,610 --> 00:00:09,200
and resistance levels when day trading.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:14,799
And determining support and resistance levels
is common problem faced by most traders.

4
00:00:14,799 --> 00:00:20,210
Some of the common methods to determine support
and resistance include trend lines, moving

5
00:00:20,210 --> 00:00:24,090
averages, pivot points, Fibonacci retracement
etc.

6
00:00:24,090 --> 00:00:30,600
Today, you will learn how to determine hidden
support and resistance levels using Fibonacci

7
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,210
extensions.

8
00:00:32,210 --> 00:00:38,300
Fibonacci series incorporates several analysis
tools on the basis of Fibonacci ratios and

9
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:43,650
sequences showing geometrical law of human
behavior and nature which is also applied

10
00:00:43,650 --> 00:00:45,640
to financial markets.

11
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:51,150
The Fibonacci study can be applied to identify
probable support and resistance levels by

12
00:00:51,150 --> 00:00:55,610
studying Fibonacci numbers in various timeframes.

13
00:00:55,610 --> 00:01:02,059
Fibonacci extensions, also referred to as
Fibonacci expansions, or Fibonacci projections,

14
00:01:02,059 --> 00:01:07,290
are external levels that go beyond the 100%
Fibonacci level.

15
00:01:07,290 --> 00:01:14,060
You may already be familiar with these important
Fibonacci levels – 23.6%, 38.2%, 50.0%,

16
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:17,100
and 61.8%.

17
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:22,560
These are considered internal retracements
that are measured inside of a specific swing

18
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:23,560
being analyzed.

19
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:30,229
But there are important Fibonacci levels that
extend beyond the 100% level and where price

20
00:01:30,229 --> 00:01:32,640
action tends to react often.

21
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:38,850
And these are what we call Fibonacci extension
levels.

22
00:01:38,850 --> 00:01:44,850
Fibonacci extension is drawn by joining three
points unlike Fibonacci retracement which

23
00:01:44,850 --> 00:01:50,049
has just two points by joining the lowest
and the highest points of a pre-defined trend

24
00:01:50,049 --> 00:01:51,290
and vice versa.

25
00:01:51,290 --> 00:01:56,830
Let’s understand how we can draw Fibonacci
extension in case of an uptrend.

26
00:01:56,830 --> 00:02:03,890
You need to join the lowest and the highest
point and then after a retracement or a correction,

27
00:02:03,890 --> 00:02:08,830
and the price continues in the direction of
the original trend, the low of the retracement

28
00:02:08,830 --> 00:02:11,620
or a pullback would be our third point.

29
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:19,050
For example, looking at this chart, the price
moved from here to here and after this the

30
00:02:19,050 --> 00:02:22,810
stock moves in the direction of the original
trend.

31
00:02:22,810 --> 00:02:30,510
So the first point to draw Fibonacci extension
would be at point a, the point b will be here

32
00:02:30,510 --> 00:02:35,319
and the third point will be here, at the low
of the retracement.

33
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:41,040
This will give you probable resistance levels
where the price may face resistance in the

34
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:42,500
near future.

35
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:45,819
Let’s now consider a downtrend.

36
00:02:45,819 --> 00:02:52,150
In this example you can see that we have a
bearish swing in price from point A to point

37
00:02:52,150 --> 00:02:56,989
B before price retraces part of this decline.

38
00:02:56,989 --> 00:03:03,400
Once price has corrected to point C and then
begun selling off again we can go ahead and

39
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:10,629
apply our extension tool, mapping the swing
from point A to point B and then back up to

40
00:03:10,629 --> 00:03:14,379
point C.
The most common Fibonacci extension levels

41
00:03:14,379 --> 00:03:21,379
are 161.8%, 261.8% and 423.6%.

42
00:03:21,379 --> 00:03:34,500
Other important resistance levels using Fibonacci
extension come at 50%, 61.8%, 78.6% and 100%.

43
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:41,550
Fibonacci extensions are a way to establish
price targets or find projected areas of support

44
00:03:41,550 --> 00:03:46,739
or resistance when the price is moving into
an area where other methods of finding support

45
00:03:46,739 --> 00:03:49,950
or resistance are not applicable or evident.

46
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:55,490
If the price moves through one extension level,
it may continue moving toward the next.

47
00:03:55,490 --> 00:04:00,349
That said, Fibonacci extensions are areas
of possible interest.

48
00:04:00,349 --> 00:04:06,680
The price may not stop and/or reverse right
at the level, but the area around it may be

49
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,680
important.

50
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:15,209
For example, the price may move just past
the 1.618 level, or pull up just shy of it,

51
00:04:15,209 --> 00:04:17,250
before changing directions.

52
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:22,119
If you are long on a stock and a new high
occurs, you can use the Fibonacci extension

53
00:04:22,119 --> 00:04:25,710
levels for an idea of where the stock may
go.

54
00:04:25,710 --> 00:04:28,099
The same is true if you’re short.

55
00:04:28,099 --> 00:04:33,770
Fibonacci extension levels can be calculated
to give you an idea on profit target placement.

56
00:04:33,770 --> 00:04:38,460
You have the option to decide whether to cover
the position at that level.

57
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:43,599
It’s important not to confuse Fibonacci
extensions with Fibonacci retracements.

58
00:04:43,599 --> 00:04:47,849
What is the difference between Fibonacci extensions
and Fibonacci retracements?

59
00:04:47,849 --> 00:04:53,320
While extensions show where the price will
go following a retracement, Fibonacci retracement

60
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:56,740
levels indicate how deep a retracement could
be.

61
00:04:56,740 --> 00:05:01,800
In other words, Fibonacci retracements measure
the pullbacks within a trend, while Fibonacci

62
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:07,150
extensions measure the impulse waves in the
direction of the trend.

63
00:05:07,150 --> 00:05:13,900
Let’s look at some of the practical examples
to gain more clarity about the concept of

64
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,339
Fibonacci extension.

65
00:05:15,339 --> 00:05:20,210
This is crude oil in the weekly timeframe
with one Fibonacci extensions drawn on the

66
00:05:20,210 --> 00:05:26,570
above chart to show number of resistance identified
using the above logic.

67
00:05:26,570 --> 00:05:34,000
At first we noticed that, the price faced
resistance at 38.2% extension and saw an immediate

68
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,379
selloff.

69
00:05:36,379 --> 00:05:43,399
Next 50% extension acted as a strong resistance,
and you can see how the price rejected that

70
00:05:43,399 --> 00:05:46,879
area, almost to the pip.

71
00:05:46,879 --> 00:05:53,789
We then have a double top at the 61.8% extension
level, again, almost to the pip.

72
00:05:53,789 --> 00:06:00,690
On its way down, observe how to price stopped
at the previous extension levels.

73
00:06:00,690 --> 00:06:05,289
This is powerful stuff, and it’s a shame
that not many traders use this tool in their

74
00:06:05,289 --> 00:06:06,289
analysis.

75
00:06:06,289 --> 00:06:12,249
Let’s move on the stock market and analyze
a downtrend on Exxon mobile chart.

76
00:06:12,249 --> 00:06:15,360
Here is the weekly time frame.

77
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:22,240
We have the starting point here, point b here
and the correction point here.

78
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:27,069
The extension levels are respected almost
religiously.

79
00:06:27,069 --> 00:06:37,629
We have rejection at 38.2% extension level,
at 50% level, at 61.8% extension and finally

80
00:06:37,629 --> 00:06:39,340
at 78.6% level.

81
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:45,659
Also, don’t neglect the fact that after
the price rejected those extension levels,

82
00:06:45,659 --> 00:06:51,309
it stopped at previous levels, offering short
opportunities for those who wanted to trade

83
00:06:51,309 --> 00:06:54,610
in the direction of the main downtrend.

84
00:06:54,610 --> 00:07:07,930
Here are other examples of Fibonacci extension
levels on different markets.

85
00:07:07,930 --> 00:07:22,879
So, how to use the fib extensions
You can consider entering the market on fib

86
00:07:22,879 --> 00:07:26,789
extensions when the price reacts to a level.

87
00:07:26,789 --> 00:07:29,250
This could be a bounce or a breakout.

88
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:35,619
If the price bounces from a Fibonacci extension
level, it is possible that price may be stalling

89
00:07:35,619 --> 00:07:36,889
or changing direction.

90
00:07:36,889 --> 00:07:43,689
In this manner, you might be able to pursue
a price move to the previous fib level.

91
00:07:43,689 --> 00:07:49,499
In some cases, you will see the price clearly
breaking thru a Fibonacci extension level.

92
00:07:49,499 --> 00:07:55,159
In this case, you may consider a trade in
the direction of the breakout and target the

93
00:07:55,159 --> 00:07:57,439
next extension level.

94
00:07:57,439 --> 00:08:03,459
Essentially, you would trade Fibonacci levels
in a similar manner to other support and resistance

95
00:08:03,459 --> 00:08:04,569
levels.

96
00:08:04,569 --> 00:08:10,229
The main difference is that fib levels are
considered hidden levels of support and resistance

97
00:08:10,229 --> 00:08:17,710
that are not clearly recognizable to non-Fibonacci
based traders.

98
00:08:17,710 --> 00:08:21,679
Stop loss order
As a general rule, you can place your stop

99
00:08:21,679 --> 00:08:26,419
loss order at the next level beyond the one
that you are trading.

100
00:08:26,419 --> 00:08:31,139
In the case when this distance may be too
far away from your entry point, then you can

101
00:08:31,139 --> 00:08:37,250
simply use a swing top/bottom that is closer
to your entry point.

102
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:41,190
Take profit level
In trading, there are no certainties.

103
00:08:41,190 --> 00:08:43,110
We are dealing with possibilities and probabilities.

104
00:08:43,110 --> 00:08:48,269
And so it is important to understand that
there is no such thing as knowing exactly

105
00:08:48,269 --> 00:08:50,829
how far a price move will go.

106
00:08:50,829 --> 00:08:55,300
You can always set a minimum target at the
next Fibonacci extension.

107
00:08:55,300 --> 00:09:00,310
However, you will see that price will very
often move farther than this, so you have

108
00:09:00,310 --> 00:09:04,410
to evaluate the market condition at each level
and act accordingly.

109
00:09:04,410 --> 00:09:11,490
You do this by taking into account other factors
such as volatility and average daily range,

110
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:15,050
which can help in setting logical take profit
targets.

111
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:20,839
The more volatile the market you are trading
is, the more likely it is to generate bigger

112
00:09:20,839 --> 00:09:22,690
moves.

113
00:09:22,690 --> 00:09:30,220
Though Fibonacci is one of the useful methods
to analyze your chart but it doesn’t provide

114
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:34,829
an exact entry point rather an estimated area
of entry.

115
00:09:34,829 --> 00:09:40,110
Moreover, there is a no guarantee that the
price will reverse from any specified fib

116
00:09:40,110 --> 00:09:46,360
level and hence you should combine it with
other technical parameters as a confirmation.

117
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:51,850
So use complementary indicators or patterns
when looking to determine one or multiple

118
00:09:51,850 --> 00:09:57,709
price targets because we don’t always know
which level the price will reverse from.

119
00:09:57,709 --> 00:10:00,850
However, this tool gives us levels to monitor.

120
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:07,410
It is then down to you to use other elements
such as confluence with other technical elements

121
00:10:07,410 --> 00:10:13,209
(trend lines, moving averages, indicator readings
or price action) to decide whether to trade

122
00:10:13,209 --> 00:10:15,560
the level.

123
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:20,740
Traders may differ in identifying the swing
high and swing low points from which the extension

124
00:10:20,740 --> 00:10:25,060
levels are drawn, so there is some subjectivity
involved here.

125
00:10:25,060 --> 00:10:29,720
But the best way around these problems is
to practice and practice!

126
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:35,100
The point is that there is no one right way
to do it, but with a lot of practice, you’ll

127
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:38,730
make better decisions of picking swing points.

128
00:10:38,730 --> 00:10:43,470
Gradually you will get a feel for the trend
and the overall technical picture.

